Sure, here are some example sentences in Serbian that use the word "priprema" in different forms and positions:

1. *Priprema* za ispit će mi oduzeti puno vremena. (*Preparation* for the exam will take up a lot of my time.)
2. Veoma je važno da imamo dobru *pripremu* za takmičenje. (It's very important to have good *preparation* for the competition.)
3. Ona je već započela *pripreme* za svoje venčanje. (She has already started *preparations* for her wedding.)
4. Zahtevaćemo detaljnu *pripremu* pre nego što krenemo na put. (We will require detailed *preparation* before we embark on the trip.)
5. *Pripremite* se da čujete neke loše vesti. (*Prepare* yourselves to hear some bad news.)
6. Moramo *pripremiti* prostoriju pre nego što gosti stignu. (We have to *prepare* the room before the guests arrive.)
7. Ona *priprema* ručak dok ja perem sudove. (She is *preparing* lunch while I do the dishes.)
8. Za ovaj posao je neophodno da se *pripremite* unapred. (For this job, it's necessary to *prepare* in advance.)

I hope this helps!